column5: There is nothing better than sitting around the table after some great camp cooking, looking at a map of the lake and comparing notes with the other boats. I like to have 4-5 copies of the lake printed out on 11x17 paper, thanks to the office printer and let everyone make some notes for this year and the future. I also laminate a copy for the boat...just in case! Whats your best free map site, this one works pretty good. 58 More Days!! http://geography.about.com/gi/dynami...5Fimage%5Fview
Here's the one I used for the same purposes.http://www.anglersatlas.com/search/
the website I use is http:/atlas.nrcan.gc.ca/site/english/maps/topo/ it takes you straight to the topo maps and you can download all your maps from here
If you want to view aerial photos and topo maps online, try this one:http://mapper.acme.com/(click on "topo" in the top right corner)it is basically an expansion to google maps.
Try this one it will list the fish species found in any lake. http://nomap.ca/(S(h5rgdn45anqhjm551ndmho3u))/Home.aspx
